<pubDate> Thu, 27 Jun 2024 14:03:48 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1719497030</ingested><modified> 2024-06-27T14:03:59+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="868" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2Fe7c7c6f0-348c-11ef-bfef-0ad696fea21d&amp;resize=1400%2C868&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=49c23eba36641d4f7a96c378e2ba99bf62591425" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="868" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2Fe7c7c6f0-348c-11ef-bfef-0ad696fea21d&amp;resize=1400%2C868&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=84c73d0175e45a87d4bbdf895267a2ca2d317754" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Blink]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Blink Outdoor 4 + Blink Mini 2]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Blink Outdoor 4 + Blink Mini 2 ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[YouTube reportedly wants to pay record labels to use their songs for AI training]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>关于人工智能的大部分讨论都围绕着使用<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/openai-admits-its-impossible-to-train-generative-ai-without-copyrighted-materials-103311496.html">受版权保护的材料来训练模型</a>。据 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.ft.com/content/e2d9472d-32e0-43f5-8109-efb753fac330">英国《</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.ft.com/content/e2d9472d-32e0-43f5-8109-efb753fac330"><em>金融时报》</em></a> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.ft.com/content/e2d9472d-32e0-43f5-8109-efb753fac330">报道，</a> YouTube 据称正在采取措施避免这一问题，向主要音乐唱片公司提供付款以授权其歌曲进行人工智能训练。</p><p>据报道，索尼音乐娱乐公司、环球音乐集团和华纳唱片公司都参与了与谷歌旗下平台的谈判。然而，这些公司不太可能拥有最终决定权，因为据报道，是否参加将由每位艺术家决定。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>许多音乐家对于让人工智能靠近他们的工作一点也不感到兴奋。 2023年4月，超过<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/us-bill-proposes-ai-companies-list-what-copyrighted-materials-they-use-123058589.html">200名艺术家签署了一封公开信</a>，表示“我们必须防止人工智能的掠夺性使用，窃取专业艺术家的声音和肖像，侵犯创作者的权利，破坏音乐生态系统。”</p><p> 11 月， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtubes-first-ai-generated-music-tools-can-clone-artist-voices-and-turn-hums-into-melodies-132025817.html">YouTube 推出了 Dream Track</a> ，该工具允许精选创作者从 John Legend 和 Charli XCX 等歌手的歌词和声音中提取歌词和声音。然而，只有十位艺术家参与了该工具的测试，而 YouTube 的目标显然是让“数十位”参与人工智能歌曲生成器。</p><p>唱片公司已经对他们看到的使用其版权内容的公司采取了立场。 6 月 24 日， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/record-labels-sue-ai-music-generators-for-massive-infringement-of-recorded-music-172915925.html">索尼、环球和华纳三人对音乐制作商 Suno 和 Omio 提起“大规模”版权侵权诉讼</a>。他们要求禁止进一步使用，并要求每件作品罚款 15 万美元。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/youtube-reportedly-wants-to-pay-record-labels-to-use-their-songs-for-ai-training-125052503.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/youtube-reportedly-wants-to-pay-record-labels-to-use-their-songs-for-ai-training-125052503.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> de7fcacb-2edb-475f-8b78-1dc4d6cd1880 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sarah Fielding]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jun 2024 12:50:52 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1719492119</ingested><modified> 2024-06-27T12:42:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Music]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="932" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F889cc560-c13f-11ee-affd-06f3a8a8a695&amp;resize=1400%2C932&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=19ca0363b35fb371dcc4b97ff222f0de91d5a1ac" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="932" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F889cc560-c13f-11ee-affd-06f3a8a8a695&amp;resize=1400%2C932&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=d274c5fad4b72ab7eaf167d29b81ab82f40f24a0" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - The YouTube app is displayed on an iPad in Baltimore. Police said Wednesday, Jan. 31, 2024, that they charged Justin Mohn, 32, with first-degree murder and abusing a corpse after he beheaded his father, Michael, in their Bucks County, Pa., home and publicized it in a 14-minute YouTube video that anyone, anywhere could see. (AP Photo/Patrick Semansky, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Father Beheaded Social Media]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google uses AI to add 110 new languages to Translate]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>虽然<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-translate-context-ai-ios-redesign-184840667.html">谷歌翻译</a>远非完美，但它仍然是获取信息或参与对话的有用方式。现在，随着<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://blog.google/products/translate/google-translate-new-languages-2024/">Google 使用 AI 提供翻译 110 种新语言</a>，例如粤语、旁遮普语 (Shahmukhi) 和 NKo，该选项正在扩展。大约四分之一的语言来自非洲，谷歌声称所有新语言总共代表了 6.14 亿使用者——约占全球人口的 8%。</p><p>谷歌将其法学硕士<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-unveils-its-multilingual-code-generating-palm-2-language-model-180805304.html">PaLM 2</a>视为“解决这个难题的关键部分，帮助 Translate 更有效地学习彼此密切相关的语言，包括接近印地语的语言，如阿瓦迪语和马尔瓦地语，以及法语克里奥尔语，如塞舌尔克里奥尔语和毛里求斯语克里奥尔语。”谷歌翻译高级软件工程师 Isaac Caswell 补充道：“随着技术的进步，以及我们继续与专家语言学家和母语人士合作，随着时间的推移，我们将支持更多的语言品种和拼写约定。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在零样本机器翻译的帮助下，谷歌翻译于 2022 年 5 月获得了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-translate-24-language-expansion-171810853.html">最后一次大量语言涌入</a>。零射击允许模型学习新语言，即使它不查看示例。同年晚些时候，谷歌宣布了 1000 种语言计划，旨在创建能够支持——你猜对了——全球最常用的 1000 种语言的人工智能模型。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/google-uses-ai-to-add-110-new-languages-to-translate-123009750.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-uses-ai-to-add-110-new-languages-to-translate-123009750.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> aab0e708-ca10-4070-a380-7ee4bbce5ecf </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sarah Fielding]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jun 2024 12:30:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1719480436</ingested><modified> 2024-06-27T09:27:20+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><